    <text id="B0313T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Batis thanks Jackson for a recommendation for a local post.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. Thos. P. Jackson,</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-02-17">February 17th 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">New Hope, Augusta <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr><abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Yours of the 10th has been <abbr expan="received">rec'd</abbr> and read. I am
                    glad you sent on my name as a Candidate for U.S. Storekeeper of one of the
                    Distilleries of Augusta <abbr expan="County">Co</abbr>. I know I can attend to
                    the business as well as any other man. Grateful for past favors, I will try and
                    be more vigilant in the discharge of all Public duties entrusted to my care, and
                    hope you will always remember me when a vacancy occurs.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>Charles Batis</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">New Hope <abbr expan="Post Office">PO</abbr><lb/>Augusta
                            <abbr expan="county">Co.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
